{
  "stem": "5551.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- but our-- out activity was building the railroads and unloading railroad cars-- freight, all kinds of freight, that the Germans needed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The camp was led by an SS officer by the name of Miller-- Miller.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Miller was fairly benign as the Germans-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in general-- as you would judge the SS at that time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he, too, was under obligation to present some brutality because apparently, this was meant as a way of maintaining an atmosphere of fear that-- that lends itself much better to control of the population.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So periodically, we would have hangings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would find a reason.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The main reason was an attempt to escape.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was invariably under death penalty.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They would call out all the prisoners early in the morning, maybe 5 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was especially bad on winter days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were not very well clothed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They would all be put-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] they would all be assembled in that square in the camp, and would witness the hanging.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Those that were hanged remained there for days so that everybody can see it and remember it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Brutality, by the way, was not something the Germans were hiding.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was something they were advertising because it spread fear, and fear lent itself much better to control.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In fact, Miller had periodic hangings for that purpose.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But we know that some of it was pressure from-- from the leadership of the SS, because there were commissions coming to review the camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "When they came, there was invariably some kind of brutality staged.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But beatings or other harassments, in general, were very few, very few under Miller.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But Miller's camp was the first one to close, and when Miller's camp closed, we were taken up to the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
